text: Even though it’s a small gallery, it’s still worth a visit as the art in there are really nice, especially the gold table which I never thought I could see at this gallery. Would recommend to anyone who’s interested to visit an art gallery. The best part, FREE ENTRY
Very interresting Gallery with very famoust Artists from all over the world......
I liked the ‘Teochew fishball noodles’ here. You can pay with a card.
Neat gallery but very small selection of modern art. Modern "art" is not really my cup of tea but I would have liked to seen  more technically advanced works, perhaps more immersive exhibits.

Nice and quiet free art gallery with surprising art pieces. I was there to see the SG Enable showcase of artwork by persons of disabilities but found that they had famous works from the likes of Marc Chagall, Auguste Robin, Henri Matisse, Pierre-Auguste Renoir too.
